Switch the diskrecovery flag on or off.

To run the database with the disk recovery option, this flag must 
be switched on, then a database dump must be made with 'tbadmin'.
NOTE: once the diskrecovery flag is switched off, the above sequence
	must be followed to switch it on again.
See the complete description in the TransBase Manuals.

   -	Command Line Syntax :  drl=on|off
